The [[acronym]] '''SMIDSY''', short for '''"sorry mate, I didn't see you"''', is used by British motorcyclists and cyclists to describe [[traffic accident|collisions]] in which a car driver fails to [[perceive]] a two-wheel user (see [[motorcycle safety]]).

TThere is good evidence that drivers may in fact see at the subconscious level, but that this is not translated to the conscious as the brain does not perceive the other as a threat, so a driver may be able to see a bipedaller, but not transfer this information into an action of adjusting their [[automobile]]. 

These collisions may be recorded as ''failure to see'', or as simply ''[[right-of-way]] violations''.  



